UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1432
1 AN ACT relating to sexual assault nurse examiners.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 211 IS CREATED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 (1) The Cabinet for Health and Family Services shall employ a health professional
6 as a statewide sexual assault nurse examiner (SANE) coordinator to support the
7 logistical operations of the SANE Program and individual SANEs credentialed
8 under Section 2 of this Act.
9 (2) The cabinet shall establish a description, essential duties, and responsibilities of
10 the SANE coordinator position that shall include but not be limited to:
11 (a) Identifying and recruiting potential SANEs across the state;
12 (b) Organizing and facilitating comprehensive SANE training programs;
13 (c) Establishing and maintaining relationships with key stakeholders such as
14 hospitals, law enforcement agencies, rape crisis advocates, and others; and
15 (d) Increasing SANE Program collaboration by creating opportunities for
16 networking and building rapport among SANE training programs.
17 (3) The cabinet shall collaborate with the Kentucky Hospital Association, the
18 Kentucky Board of Nursing, the Sexual Assault Response Team Advisory
19 Committee, and any other entities deemed appropriate by the cabinet, to develop a
20 statewide strategic plan that utilizes a regional model to ensure SANE coverage
21 for all Kentucky hospitals. The strategic plan shall be submitted to the Legislative
22 Research Commission for referral to the Interim Joint Committee on Health
23 Services by December 1, 2026.
24 (4) The cabinet shall develop a state registry of SANEs and make it accessible from
25 the cabinet's website by registered SANEs and Kentucky hospitals. The registry
26 shall be operational by December 1, 2026.
27 Section 2. KRS 314.142 is amended to read as follows:
Page 1 of 2
