UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1432
1 (1) The Kentucky Board of Nursing shall promulgate administrative regulations
2 pursuant to KRS Chapter 13A to create a Sexual Assault Nurse Examiner Program.
3 These administrative regulations shall address, at a minimum:
4 (a) Educational requirements for sexual assault nurse examiners and statewide
5 standards for provision of the education;
6 (b) The application process through which registered nurses who submit
7 documentation of required education and clinical experience and who remit
8 the designated application fee may apply to the board to be credentialed as a
9 "Sexual Assault Nurse Examiner";
10 (c) Continuing education requirements for maintenance of the sexual assault
11 nurse examiner credential;
12 (d) Methods of monitoring overall program implementation; and
13 (e) Procedures for obtaining input from the Sexual Assault Response Team
14 Advisory Committee established under KRS Chapter 403 prior to proposing
15 amendments to any provision of the administrative regulations promulgated
16 under this section or KRS 314.131.
17 (2) Any person in this state who holds a credential as a Sexual Assault Nurse Examiner
18 as defined in KRS 314.011(14) shall have the right to use the title "Sexual Assault
19 Nurse Examiner" and the abbreviation "SANE". No other person shall assume the
20 title or use the abbreviation or any other words, letters, signs, or figures to indicate
21 that the person using the same is a Sexual Assault Nurse Examiner.
22 (3) The board shall notify each newly registered SANE that the state registry of
23 SANEs is available on the cabinet's website as required in Section 1 of this Act.
